Source-Makefile: feeds/packages/libs/libshout/Makefile

Package: libshout
Version: 2.4.1-1
Depends: +libc +GCC_LIBSSP:libssp +USE_GLIBC:librt +USE_GLIBC:libpthread +libvorbisidec +libpthread +libopenssl
Conflicts: 
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Build-Variant: notheora
Section: libs
Category: Libraries
Repository: base
Title: Shoutcast client library (no theora)
Maintainer: Nicolas Thill <nico@openwrt.org>, Ted Hess <thess@kitschensync.net>
Source: libshout-2.4.1.tar.gz
License: LGPL-2.0+
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Type: ipkg
Description:    libshout allows applications to easily communicate and broadcast
 to an Icecast streaming media server. It handles the socket connections,
 metadata communication, and data streaming for the calling application,
 and lets developers focus on feature sets instead of implementation
 details.
  .
  This package does not have Theora support.
http://www.icecast.org
Nicolas Thill <nico@openwrt.org>, Ted Hess <thess@kitschensync.net>
@@

